# Compiler-facing language reference

Language semantics are moving from the consolidated language overview into
focused canonical Beandown references. Use this map to find the current owner
for each concept.

## Migrated concepts

### Loops

- `docs/src/docs/loops/conditional-loops.bd`
- `docs/src/docs/loops/collection-loops.bd`
- `docs/src/docs/loops/range-loops.bd`
- `docs/src/docs/loops/loop-control.bd`

The unsuffixed files above own exact loop semantics.

Their paired `-basic.bd` files provide simplified teaching versions. The public
route combines both levels:

`docs/src/docs/loops/#page.bst`

## Remaining language authority

`docs/language-overview.md` remains the canonical compiler-facing reference for
every language concept not listed under Migrated concepts.

A migrated section in the consolidated overview points to its new canonical
files instead of retaining a second copy of the rules.

## Public documentation

`docs/src/docs/**` contains website pages, teaching references, examples and
topic navigation.

## Design boundaries

`docs/src/docs/codebase/design-scope/overview.bd` summarises accepted
mechanisms, constraints and intentionally excluded complexity.

## Memory access

`docs/src/docs/codebase/memory-management/access-and-aliasing/overview.bd`
covers shared reads, explicit copies and `~` access.

## Compiler ownership

`docs/src/docs/codebase/compiler-design/overview.bd` routes language features
to the compiler stages and subsystems that implement them.
